data.name: checkBoxPermittedProcessStrongKill.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether a process may be killed in a not-nice way, which may cause data loss if the application had unsaved data in memory or was just writing to a persistent memory/drive. If application is safe to be killed anytime this avoids bothering users.

data.name: textBoxPermittedProcessPath.ToolTip
data.value: Filesystem path (formatted system specific) to the process executable's directory excluding the filename, see field executable. If the path is not given or relative, then SEB searches the system provided paths for applications.

data.name: checkBoxPermittedProcessAllowUser.ToolTip
data.value: Users can locate the third party application with a file dialog if it cannot be found at the paths specified. Only applications matching the other criteria specified (like executable, identifier, signature) are accepted.

data.name: checkBoxAllowFlashFullscreen.ToolTip
data.value: Playing videos with Flash in full screen mode is a security problem, it is recommended to use HTML5 video instead of Flash. When switching to third party applications is disabled, Flash fullscreen mode isn't possible at all.

data.name: textBoxProhibitedProcessUser.ToolTip
data.value: Username under which this process is running. If no user is indicated, then the process is killed regardless under which user it's running. Instead of this identifier also check box current user can be used.

data.name: checkBoxProhibitedProcessStrongKill.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether a process may be killed in a not-nice way, which may cause data loss if the application had unsaved data in memory or was just writing to a persistent memory/drive. If application is safe to be killed anytime this avoids bothering users.

data.name: listBoxChooseFileToUploadPolicy.ToolTip
data.value: SEB can let the user choose the file to upload manually (as usual) or automatically choose the same file which was downloaded before. If the file is not found, a file requester or an error is presented depending on this setting.

data.name: checkBoxHideBrowserWindowToolbar.ToolTip
data.value: Hide browser window toolbar by default. Users can unhide it in the view menu or the contextual menu on the browser window title bar. In full screen browser view mode, toolbar is auto hidden with this setting and appears when the mouse is moved towards the screen’s top border.

data.name: comboBoxCryptoIdentity.ToolTip
data.value: Identities (X.509 certificates with RSA public key and associated private key) in the Windows Certificate Store which can be used for encrypting and decrypting. Export the chosen identity and install it on your (managed) SEB clients.

data.name: radioButtonConfiguringAClient.ToolTip
data.value: A SEB settings file saved with this option can be used to change the local settings of a SEB client. Encrypt it with the same password which is set as administrator password on the SEB client (or none if there is no administrator password set yet). Other passwords will be prompted.

data.name: textBoxQuitPassword.ToolTip
data.value: This password is prompted when users try to quit SEB with the Quit button, Ctrl-Q or the red close button in the browser window. The password is not prompted when using a quit link in the exam system.

data.name: checkBoxAllowQuit.ToolTip
data.value: If selected, Users can quit SEB with the Quit button in the SEB taskbar, by pressing the keys Ctrl-Q or by clicking the main browser window (the one that displays the exam) close button. Otherwise you can use a quit link in your exam system or shutdown or reboot the computer.
